# Explicitly allow YAML and JSON files (used for frontmatter / CMS content).
# These negations are listed first; the specific Obsidian ignores below are listed
# last and therefore take final precedence over these negations for their exact paths.
!**/*.yaml
!**/*.yml
!**/*.json

# Obsidian state — workspace layout and cache are machine-specific and should not be tracked.
# Listed after the negation rules above so Git applies these as the winning (last) rule.
.obsidian/workspace.json
.obsidian/workspace-mobile.json
.obsidian/cache

# OS and editor noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
